Christine1946-
Hi. I'm from the Prostate Cancer Forum here on Healingwell. (I'm a survivor of that who posts there, but sometimes I read posts in the other Healingwell forums as well).
If you go to the Google search box at 
and type in
ovarian cancer forums
you will retrieve an index screen offering some possibilities for what you are looking for. In particular, one forum on ovarian cancer hosted by the Cancer Survivors Network that looks promising is:
Good luck.
Age: 71
Chronic prostatitis (age 60 on)
BPH w/ urinary obstruction, 6/2011
TURP, 7/2011
Ongoing high PSA, 7/2011-12/2011
Biopsy, 12/2011: positive 3/12 (90%, 70%, 5%)
Gleason 6(3+3), T1c
No mets, PCa likely still organ contained
IMRT w/ HT (Lupron), 4/2012-6/2012
PSAs (since post-IMRT): 0.1 or lower
Posts.Title: Don't know where else to post.
